# Command easydocker

## What does this command do:

EasyDocker is a TUI focused on investigating and troubleshooting Docker resources. Highly inspired by lazydocker and k9s while leveraging beautiful graphics from BubbleTea. Like k9s command.

## Installed from

For Fedora install using: export EASYDOCKER_INSTALL_DIR=~/.local/bin && curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/joao-zanutto/easydocker/main/install/install.sh | sh
For Raspberry Pi install using: export EASYDOCKER_INSTALL_DIR=~/.local/bin && curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/joao-zanutto/easydocker/main/install/install.sh | sh
For Mac install using: curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/joao-zanutto/easydocker/main/install/install.sh | sh

## Command path

For Fedora run: ~/.local/bin/easydocker
For Raspberry Pi run: ~/.local/bin/easydocker
For Mac run: /usr/local/bin/easydocker

## Command documentation

Docs can be found at https://github.com/joao-zanutto/easydocker

## Command options

easydocker          # launch the TUI

### Browse Mode (main view)
# ←/h / →/l       navigate between tabs
# ↑/k / ↓/j       move selection up/down
# pgup / pgdn      jump by page
# a                toggle between running and all resources
# Enter            open logs for selected container
# /                activate filter
# Esc              return to previous screen or quit

### Logs Mode
# ←/→             scroll logs horizontally
# ↑/k / ↓/j       move through log lines
# pgup/pgdn/home/end  navigate full log buffer
# f                toggle follow mode (auto-scroll to new entries)
# w                toggle line wrapping
# /                search within logs
# Esc              close logs view
